data.name: LogLevel
desc: specifies levels to distinguish between severities of logged events

items.name: OFF
lines: specifies that no messages are to be logged at all
This level can be set at an XLogger to completely prevent logging. You will usually not use it with a concrete log event.

items.name: SEVERE
lines: denotes a serious failure to be logged

items.name: WARNING
lines: denotes a potential problem to be logged

items.name: INFO
lines: denotes an informational message to be logged

items.name: CONFIG
lines: denotes a static configuration message to be logged

items.name: FINE
lines: denotes basic tracing information to be logged

items.name: FINER
lines: denotes more fine-grained tracing information to be logged

items.name: FINEST
lines: denotes highly detailed tracing information to be logged

items.name: ALL
lines: specifies that all messages should be logged
This level can be set at an XLogger to enable logging of absolutely all events. You will usually not use it with a concrete log event.
